<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :bluejump --><img src=http://www.tribalfury.org/emoticons/bluejump.gif ALT=":bluejump"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">If you need a raid that is an EPIC hit - don't post in this thread. </span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :bluejump --><img src=http://www.tribalfury.org/emoticons/bluejump.gif ALT=":bluejump"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The ONLY epic hits </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that I plan for - are those that are for members that have a post in the epic checklist thread in the Epic forum.  Because in my opinion - if you don't post in that thread - you don't want guild help on your epic.<br>
<br>
Also - if you change what places you would like to recomend a raid for - edit your original post - like to keep this thread from getting HUGE.<br>
<br>
Also - if there is anything unusual about your raid - post a link to any research you did/found for the area... please no 2000 word strategys in this thread.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I would also like to invite ALL tf members to gauge interest for help by starting your own 1 to 2 group activities in open forum and epic forum for small hits.   People used to do this but now seem to either - want to use a raid day or grumble about LFG.   A good example for this is Seb, Trials, Charm hunting, CoM, hole, rare spawn camps etc that you need help on to finish a quest but isn't really within the formula that we have for raids of 3 groups or more.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
we would like to keep the guild raid board from becoming too confusing with tons of peeps starting raids all the time.  please ONLY use Thursday raids as the open to any Raid leader days.<br>
<br>
Currently Friday and saturday raids are reserved for larger raids led by people on Jahras's approved list and focused on the tougher end of some epics and gear upgrades.  <br>
<br>
Our current formula is 1st, 3rd Friday is gear up grade raids led by pensfan. On the 2nd Saturday - I (Serano) ussually lead a LARGE raid to do something hard.  the other 1st and 3rd saturdays I will raid something sometimes - but it is also open for other events as well.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :bluejump --><img src=http://www.tribalfury.org/emoticons/bluejump.gif ALT=":bluejump"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btribalfury31319.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seranotf>SeranoTF</A> at: 4/20/03 4:33:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btribalfury31319.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deladriendil>Deladriendil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Fier'Dal</span><br>  Posts: 621<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/03 1:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: REQUEST your raid here!! ALSO RAID Formula/ recomendatio</span><hr size=1> also might want to add that the last week of the month is an XP week and raids are not scheduled then...<br>
