<br>
1.) Revamped Hate - Why? We spent a week farming mage epic crowns that caused 1/2 the guild to develop bixie/sphinx phobias. Let's finish this up. I'm also aware of other neat drops desired by members in the guild here, including the Maestro's bard loot and my favorite, the SEoC. <br>
<br>
2.) Cazic Thule in Fear. - Why? Two reasons. First, he drops some nice loot that would help our casters out alot, especially his brain. Second, he's doable. He's perhaps the only old world god left that we can do since Inny has been tweaked and the majority of the guild won't sacrifice their Tunare faction. We've never killed a diety before, and I think this would be a very nice step forward. Oh, and I almost forgot- DRACOLICHE revenge~!<br>
<br>
3.) Ssra Temple Farming - Why? Ssra is where we move after ToV. Ssra and ToV will obtain us the gear we need to raid the upper tier planes. However, Ssra is time consuming, ESPECIALLY w/ bane weapons and emperor keys. Also, the majority of people have never even been inside the zone, much less know it like the people I've taken along. It'll be a good experience and it's a relaxing change from our usual routines. Pickups are hard to do, and I think after 1 or 2 guild sponsered outings, people will be more inclined to this zone.  <br>
<br>
4.) PoI Dragon - Why? Because we can. We have the force. We can do this. This is probably the easiest PoP flag boss mob and would be a good step forward for us. Mobs like Dozer, Grummus, and our dragon pal here have nasty AoE's which we as a guild arent used to yet. Ssra boss mobs also have these. We need to work on this. Practice, flaggage, loot, and taking out a PoP boss mob. Need I say more? ^_^ <br>
<br>
5.) Minis in BoT - Why? Spectral Parchements and Glyphed Rune Words. Tell me you casters and hybrids really want to spend hundreds of thousands of K of PP to get your 63-65  spells, even if they were avalible in the bazaar. Or.... we could do this.... <br>
<br>
6.) Minis in Plane of Storms - Why? I mentioned BoT before this for a reason. This is perhaps the most managable planar raid we can do and perhaps the first we should attempt. It'd be open to all 55+, results in specs, some uber tier 2 loot, and grants flaggage for a free aa and a stronger charm. Also the more people we have in BoT = more specs and runed words. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
